An Act regularizing water rates for tenants.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 22 of chapter 186 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting in subsection (g) after the words “water
3 consumption for the entire premises” the following:
4 “, Multiplied by each individual submeter’s applicable municipal rate determined by each
5 submetered unit’s total individual usage.”
6 SECTION 2. Said section 22 of chapter 186, as so appearing, is hereby further amended
7 by inserting in subsection (g) after the words “shown on such bill or invoice” the following:
8 “The landlord shall be responsible for all additional water costs resulting from increased
9 municipal rates due to the total water usage of the entire premises.”
